{
  "texts": [
    "The triple facts are denoted by ( e 1, r, e 2), where e 1 is the subject, e 2 is the object, and r is the relationship between the two.",
    "The first layer of the model projects a pair of entities from the input into low-dimensional vectors, and the second layer combines these two vectors into a scalar to be compared by a scoring function.",
    "Entity representation learning can be defined as:where f can be a linear/nonlinear function, W is a parameter matrix, W can be initialized randomly/pre-trained, and X is a one-hot/n-hot vector representing the input entities e 1 and e 2.",
    "DistMult was empirically evaluated for link prediction tasks on the Free- base dataset.",
    "The results showed that a bilinear model successfully captures the compositional semantics of the relationships."
  ]
}